⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Dead Partner
node GDS · GDS · ⟦The Dead Partner:GDS:a690e9⟧

WHO   — The Dead Partner — the grief Don runs from
WHAT  — The wound under the hustle: the recklessness and grief the rootless man is outrunning, played as a cameo gag with a real ache beneath.
WHERE — GDS · The Goods (2009)  Framework inputs: The Goods: Live Hard, Sell Hard (2009, dir. Neal Brennan, Gary Sanchez/Paramount Vantage); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the closer's restlessness has a cause, and the dead partner is it.
HOW   — By dying on Don's watch and becoming the guilt that keeps him moving and unable to stay.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  He killed me with a joke — sex toys where the parachute should've been — and then ran from town to town so he'd never have to land.

